	   <tr><td colspan=2>yah, I know I am a Transport class. But I have a personal pet peeve.<br><br>Today I log on and head to SEB. Shout &quot;Druid 55 LFG&quot;<br><br>First thing I see is &quot;can you port me?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Not really I reply I just got here and am looking for a group&quot;<br><br>&quot;Cant you just bind here and come back?&quot; He asks.<br><br>&quot;cant bind in here &quot; I say.<br><br>&quot;yah , but you can run to Zone out, bind near orb then come back in and port me&quot; <br><br>I was so freaking shocked at the very idea that i just gave up and did what he said. It was obvious he didnt give a rat's rear what I wanted. He just wanted a port. I was more then happy to get his silly arse out of the dam zone.<br>I really Felt like just blowing up, something along the lines of &quot;WTF.. am i not supposed to get exp? am i just here to move your arse's around? Cant you make a freaking Thug Gate potion?&quot;<br>I was seriously mad. And the stupid thing is, this happens lots to me. I zone into a high lvl zone looking for a group and before I get one I get 10 tells asking for a port. What is wrong with people, do they not give a crap, or are they just so self centred they think we should just drop whatever were doing and port them?<br>any input?<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Regnon Plainswalker Lvl 63 Druid of NIHIL Bertox<br>What the heck was that?.....darn bixie stinger</td></tr>
